The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, June 20, 2004 				Metro Recommends

	THE VCD 
	(MusicWorld, Rs 199) Its won a variety of labels, from best Hollywood movie of all time, to Americas most popular and beloved movie. The doomed love story between Humphrey Boggart and Ingrid Bergman set against the backdrop of World War II lives on for its magic moments and immortal lines. So, play it again (and again and again) Sam. THE EVENT				 																																	(Swabhumi, till June 27) Sample some of the culinary delicacies from Orissa, enjoy the folk theatre, dance and handicrafts, and grab a holiday offer with The Telegraph Hotspot coupon. The Rathayatra mood just adds to the excitement. THE GAME				 																																	(June 22, 12.10 am, ESPN/Star Sports) Its gone down to the wire in Group B. This crunch match pits David Beckham (below) and his star-studded squad against a never-say-die Croat side. Watch out for the 18-year-old Wayne Rooney, the newest striking sensation who has already become the youngest to score a Euro goal. 

